              <title>Workshop activity 1: Mapping the context</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/6370</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/6370</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>There has already been some discussion about what models and tools we might use to help us review and articulate the design problem space in advance starting of any MOOC design work proper. So far the models on the table are:</p>
<p>Simon Cross's <a href="http://latestendeavour.wordpress.com/2010/07/05/the-lattice-model-for-designing-learning-defining-the-design-problem-space-and-guiding-the-design-solutions/">Lattice Model</a> and Yishay Mor's <a href="https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1BneOQmlmG6ZQFUIjVWehA487g7-_-Gpi36-d41rzlwY/edit">Scenario/ Force map</a> tool</p>
<p>To summarise our discussions so far, I think that we feel that Simon's lattice model is too complicated to use in an activity, so we think we will probably use Yishay's activity and then review activity outputs using the Lattice Model (correct me if I'm wrong anyone!) so that we can begin to locate priorities and concerns.</p>
<p>Do you know of any other learning design tools we might use to define the problem space at this early stage? Please join in :-)</p>]]></description>
